489	\section{Use in the project}
490	
491	The composition of the four typeclass instances of Sections~\ref{sec:moduleK_prereqs}–\ref{sec:moduleK_ext}, Definition~\ref{def:Scheme_toModuleKSheaf}, and Definition~\ref{def:Scheme_HModule} delivers Phase~A step~5 in full and bridges to Phase~A step~6:
492	
493	\begin{itemize}
494	  \item For $C : \Over\,(\Spec\,(\CommRingCat\,k))$, the $\ModuleCat\,k$-flavoured cohomology
495	    \[
496	      H^n_{\Module\,k}(C, \struct C) \;:=\; \mathtt{HModule}\,k\,(\toModuleKSheaf\,C)\,n
497	    \]
498	    is well-defined and automatically carries a $\Module\,k$ instance, so $\Module.\mathtt{finrank}\,k\,(\HModule\,k\,(\toModuleKSheaf\,C)\,1) : \mathbb N$ is well-defined.
499	  \item The forgetful functor $\ModuleCat\,k \to \AddCommGrpCat$ recovers the iter-004 abelian-group cohomology (Definition~\ref{def:Scheme_toModuleKSheaf_forgetCompare}), so the new $\HModule$ commutes with the existing $\Sheaf.\mathtt H$ on the underlying type level.
500	  \item Phase~A step~6 (Serre finiteness, $\finrank_k H^i(C, \mathcal F) < \infty$) remains the deep work to come, but is now expressible inside Mathlib's standard $\Module\,k$ API: the statement of Serre finiteness becomes a $\Module.\mathtt{Finite}\,k\,(\HModule\,k\,F\,n)$ predicate.
501	\end{itemize}
